:2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705185,"age":41,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Ivo de Vesci, Lord of Alnwick was born in 1065, in Malton, Yorkshire, England as the son of Yvo de Vesci II. He married Ada Tyson in 1086, in York, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He lived in Alnwick Castle, Northumberland, England in 1095. He died in 1157, in Wales, at the age of 92."},"et":{"1065–1157":"1065–1157","1055–Male":"1055–Surnud","1065–Male":"1065–Surnud","1072–Male":"1072–Surnud","1063–1120":"1063–1120","1094–1123":"1094–1123","1030–Male":"1030–Surnud","about 1096":"umbes 1096","1066":"1066","1055":"1055","1065":"1065","1120":"1120","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1030":"1030","1063":"1063","1094":"1094","1072":"1072","1106":"1106","1157":"1157","1123":"1123","Malton, Yorkshire, England":"Malton, Yorkshire, England","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Alnwick Castle, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Alnwick Castle, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Knaresborough, Yorkshire, England":"Knaresborough, Yorkshire, England","Wales":"Wales","Alnwick Castle, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick Castle, Northumberland, England"},"fi":{"1065–1157":"1065–1157","1055–Male":"1055–Kuollut","1065–Male":"1065–Kuollut","1072–Male":"1072–Kuollut","1063–1120":"1063–1120","1094–1123":"1094–1123","1030–Male":"1030–Kuollut","ab